<problem>
<p>We say \(X_A\) is an indicator variable for event \(A\) if:</p>
  <p>\begin{align*}
        I=\begin{cases}
          1 &amp; A\text{ occurs}\\
          0 &amp; A^c\text{ occurs}
        \end{cases}
      \end{align*}</p>
  <p>If \(P(A)=0.35\), what is:</p>

<ul><li>\(E(X_A)\)</li></ul>
<numericalresponse answer="0.35">
<responseparam type="tolerance" default="0.001"/>
  <formulaequationinput />
  <solution>
  	<div class="detailed-solution">
  		<p>Explanation</p>
  		<p>\(E(X_A)\) = (0.35*1) + (0.65*0) = 0.35</p>
  	</div>
  </solution>
</numericalresponse>

<ul><li>\(V(X_A)\)</li></ul>
<numericalresponse answer="0.2275">
<responseparam type="tolerance" default="0.001"/>
  <formulaequationinput />
    <solution>
  	<div class="detailed-solution">
  		<p>Explanation</p>
  		<p>\(V(X_A)\) = \(E(X_A^2)\) - \(E(X_A)\)<sup>2</sup> </p>
  		<p>\(V(X_A)\) = 0.35 - (0.35<sup>2</sup>) = 0.2275 </p>
  	</div>
  </solution>
</numericalresponse>

</problem>